cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.MA, cs.RO

This paper focuses on developing an agent to play a competitive game in a multi-agent setting, using a combination of imitation learning and reinforcement learning. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The game involves strategic decision-making and competition, which also relates to game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the multi-agent aspect of the game involves coordination and communication, which falls under multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the game involves navigating a complex environment, which relates to robotics (cs.RO).
